TOKYO -LRB- AP -RRB- A strong earthquake with a preliminary magnitude of 7.8 struck Bougainville , Papua New Guinea on Wednesday , and was followed by a large aftershock , Japan 's Central Meteorological Agency said Thursday .
The quake was centered at a depth of about 30 kilometers -LRB- 18.6 miles -RRB- in the Solomon Sea , some 56 kilometers -LRB- 35 miles -RRB- north of Sohano , a town on the island of Bougainville .
It occurred at 7:35 p.m. -LRB- 1035 GMT -RRB- , the agency said .
An aftershock with a preliminary magnitude of 7.2 rocked the same region at 8:18 am Thursday -LRB- 2318 GMT Wednesday -RRB- , the agency said .
Other , smaller aftershocks continued to jolt the area , but there were no fears of tsunamis , seismic waves caused by undersea disturbances such as earthquakes or volcanic activity .
A magnitude 7.8 is considered capable of causing widespread damage in populated areas .
